  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ENHANCING COMPREHENSIVE SEXUAL AND GENDER BASED SERVICES FOR MARGINALIZED GROUPS</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.	     Support survivors of SGBV to access comprehensive SRH assistance, psychosocial support through counselling and legal assistance through pro bono legal advice and referral      .      
2.	Socio-economical support for marginalized groups through provision of      personal protective equipment, sanitary towels      and cash transfers.
3.	Continued advocacy and awareness with duty bearers,       community and other stakeholders regarding prevention and response services for GBV survivors with a focus on access to justice, establishment/provision of safe spaces/shelters, provision of personal protection equipment (PPE`s) to GBV service providers on the frontline attending to GBV survivors.
4.	Provision of feedback and complaint collection framework.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project&#x2019;s overall goal is to enhance comprehensive SGBV services for marginalized groups. It will focus on women and girls, women and girls with disabilities, their caregivers and out-of-school girls. This will be achieved through supporting survivors of violence access health, SGBV and socio-economic services and advocating for prevention and response services for SGBV survivors</narrative>
  </description>
